Sec. 146.021. DEPARTMENT FACILITIES. The department may
receive and hold for processing animals and animal products
transported in international trade and may establish and collect
reasonable fees for yardage, maintenance, feed, medical care,
facility use, and other necessary expenses incurred in the course of
processing those animals. Notwithstanding any other law, the
department may use any portion of fees collected under this section
that remains after spending the proceeds of the fees to meet other
necessary expenses incurred under this section for expenses related
to maintenance of or repairs to department facilities.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1367, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 2003, 78th Leg., ch. 200, Sec. 4(a), eff. Sept. 1,
2003; Acts 2003, 78th Leg., ch. 369, Sec. 9, eff. Sept. 1, 2003.

